+# Roblox Studio Profile Architecture
+
+## Boundary
+
+```text
+Authorized Roblox Studio bridge
+        │ signed activation envelope
+        ▼
+Generic SignalCore profile loader
+        ▼
+Roblox Studio domain profile
+        ├─ TaskState encoder and ambiguity gate
+        ├─ Capability graph
+        ├─ Engine/model/certification registries
+        ├─ Evidence Ledger and context knapsack
+        ├─ Workflow/checkpoint/repair planner
+        ├─ Budget/privacy/risk policies
+        └─ Telemetry and replay
+        │
+        ▼
+External Roblox/Luau/asset/animation/Blender/test engines
+```
+
+SignalCore does not execute the domain engines. It selects them, validates declared
+capabilities and pinned versions, prepares bounded inputs, compiles acceptance tests,
+and refuses success without external verifier evidence.
+
+## Module mapping
+
+| Master requirement | Implementation |
+|---|---|
+| TaskState V2 | `types.py`, `task_encoder.py` |
+| Capability graph | `capability_graph.py`, `capabilities.json` |
+| Engine/model registries | `registries.py`, `engines.example.json`, `models.example.json` |
+| Certification | `certification.py`, `certification.example.json` |
+| Deterministic skip and routing | `routing.py` |
+| Ambiguity/risk gates | `task_encoder.py`, `governance.py` |
+| Workflow/checkpoint/repair | `workflow.py` |
+| Evidence/delta/multimodal/knapsack | `evidence.py` |
+| Budget/privacy/telemetry/trace | `governance.py` |
+| Model/engine response validation | `validators.py` |
+| Signed runtime integration | existing `activation.py`, new `runtime.py` |
+| A/B/C/D evaluation | `benchmark.py` and top-level benchmark wrapper |
+
+## Fail-closed order
+
+1. Verify the signed Studio activation envelope.
+2. Encode a compact task state without conversation history.
+3. Resolve ambiguity, capabilities, dependencies and conflicts.
+4. Verify engine/model certification and sandbox availability.
+5. Select fresh evidence and build the context capsule.
+6. Reserve token, request, transfer, GPU and wall-time budgets.
+7. Compile a DAG with acceptance, retry and rollback rules.
+8. Validate every external response identity, version, capability and artifact hash.
+9. Require independent validators for high-impact outputs.
+10. Mark success only after verifier evidence is recorded.
+
+## Adaptive policy
+
+Adaptive policy mutation is disabled. `AdaptivePolicyGate` only reports whether
+stable telemetry would permit a future learning process. It cannot weaken ambiguity,
+risk, certification, sandbox, validation, privacy or human-approval invariants.
