+# Migration Notes
+
+## Compatibility
+
+- `profile.json` retains generic `schema_version: 1`, so the existing profile loader
+  remains compatible.
+- `profile_id`, `profile_version`, hidden discovery and signed activation behavior are
+  unchanged.
+- Existing activation envelope fields and nonce/process checks are unchanged.
+- Orchestration metadata is additive through `orchestration_schema_version: 2`.
+
+## Existing integrations
+
+Existing bridges can continue to load and authorize the profile. To use the new
+orchestrator, the bridge should call `create_profile_runtime()` after successful
+`load_profile()` and supply measured certification records.
+
+## State
+
+New persistent files are created under the caller-supplied SignalCore state root:
+
+```text
+roblox_studio/evidence-v3.db
+roblox_studio/telemetry-v2.db
+```
+
+They do not modify Roblox projects. Checkpoints and content-addressed payloads should
+also be stored outside the source repository.
+
+## Breaking behavior by design
+
+A non-deterministic task that previously relied on implicit engine/model authority is
+now blocked until explicit certification exists. High-risk tasks require the declared
+sandbox and human review. Full-project cloud upload remains forbidden.
